#!/usr/bin/env python3

# git-x
# Produce a git commit with three random emoji for a commit message
# Copyright (C) 2022 Ryan Finnie
# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

# Usage: git x -a
#
# The name comes from the fact that, when working on a sub-branch I
# intend to squash later, I have a tendency to do this a lot:
#   git commit -a -m x
# This is functionally the same thing, just more interesting.

